<b>Causes of sciatica</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sciatica occurs when the sciatic nerve is pinched, usually when a disk in the spin is herniated or when a bone on the bone spur (vertebrae) overgrows. On rare occasions, the sciatic nerves may be caused by diseases like diabetes.</span>

