<b>Risk factors of Sciatica</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Some factors trigger the occurrence of Sciatica. They include:</span>

<b>Age: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">The most common cause of Sciatica is age. Age causes changes in the spine such as bone spurs and herniated disks.</span>

<b>Obesity: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Excess weight on the spine can result in spinal changes which trigger sciatica.</span>

<b>Nature of job: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">If your job requires you to carry heavy loads, twist your back, or drive a vehicle for a longer time, chances are you may develop Sciatica. However, there‚Äôs no conclusive evidence to back up this observation.</span>

<b>Lengthened sitting: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Those who spend much time on a seat or live a sedentary lifestyle have higher chances of developing Sciatica unlike active people.</span>

<b>Diabetes: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Diabetes which affects how the body uses sugar can ultimately damage the nerve.</span>

