<span style="font-weight: 400;">To maintain a strong back, pay close attention to important muscles like those in your lower back and abdomen. They play a key role in postures and alignments.</span>

<b>Maintain a proper sitting posture</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Choose seats with good armrest, accurate lower back support, and a swivel base.</span>

<b>Practice good body mechanism</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">When lifting a heavy object, allow your lower extremities to take charge. If the object is way too heavy, find a lifting partner. Don‚Äôt lift and twist simultaneously.</span>

